<p><b>Raymond Charles "Ray" LaMontagne</b> (pronounced <span title="Pronunciation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA_for_English" title="Wikipedia:IPA for English">/lɑːmɒnˈteɪːn/</a></span>) (born June 18, 1973) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Singer-songwriter" title="Singer-songwriter" class="mw-redirect">singer-songwriter</a> who lives on a farm in Maine with his wife and two sons. Reportedly, after hearing a <a href="/wiki/Stephen_Stills" title="Stephen Stills">Stephen Stills</a> song, LaMontagne decided to quit his job at a shoe factory and pursue a career in music. He has since released three albums, <i><a href="/wiki/Trouble_(Ray_LaMontagne_album)" title="Trouble (Ray LaMontagne album)">Trouble</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Till_the_Sun_Turns_Black" title="Till the Sun Turns Black">Till the Sun Turns Black</a></i> and <i><a href="/wiki/Gossip_in_the_Grain" title="Gossip in the Grain">Gossip in the Grain</a></i>. In the UK, <i>Trouble</i> was a top 5 hit, and the <a href="/wiki/Trouble_(Ray_LaMontagne_song)" title="Trouble (Ray LaMontagne song)">title track of the album</a> was a top 25 hit. <i>Till the Sun Turns Black</i> was a top 40 hit in the US. A soft-spoken person who is known for his raspy voice, LaMontagne has won a number of awards for his music and has performed at several charity events.</p>
